                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d444">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1164 University of Shanghai/29:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lochhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-01T22:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 1, 1938—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 1—5:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>753. My No. 644, May 11, 4 p.m.<note n="36" xml:id="d444fn36">Not printed.</note>
                    Reference paragraph 3 regarding the return of the property of the American
                    Southern Baptist Mission on Paohsing Road.</p>
                <p>I am pleased to report that the above-mentioned property was formally returned by
                    the Japanese authorities to the mission this morning in the presence of the
                    treasurer and two other representatives of the mission, representatives of the
                    Japanese military and consular authorities and a representative of this
                    office.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Hankow, Peiping and Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
